byline.original: By MATT SIEGEL and KEVIN DREW
byline.contributor: Matt Siegel reported from Sydney, and Kevin Drew from Hong Kong.

abstract: Australia’s national carrier Qantas Airways keeps its worldwide fleet grounded as government officials and business and labor leaders say they are working to end a dispute between the airline and its employees that has left at least 80,000 passengers stranded.
